WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.640 --> 00:00:10.400
On April 2, 2014, two dutch girls, 21 year old Kris Kremers and 22 year old Lisanne Froon, were discovered missing at Boquete, Panama.

00:00:11.640 --> 00:00:17.240
Their disappearance resulted in the biggest search operation ever undertaken in Panama.

00:00:20.680 --> 00:00:27.680
Teams, helicopters, and dogs searched 1000 kilometers of trails in a wide area around Boquete.

00:00:29.600 --> 00:00:40.080
They searched for two full weeks, and they found absolutely NOTHING. Not a single trace of the two missing girls.

00:00:53.920 --> 00:01:01.920
After two weeks, the search teams ran out of options. "If the girls were anywhere in this area, we would have found them!"

00:01:05.239 --> 00:01:14.040
But if the two girls did not suffer some kind of accident, or became lost in the forest, as was originally presumed, what could have happened to them?

00:02:23.760 --> 00:02:33.000
In total shock, Marcus tells his story to the park ranger at the start of the trail, however when SINAFRONT, the border police arrives they find nothing suspicious.

00:02:34.120 --> 00:02:42.640
The next morning, a team from SINAPROC once again searches the place and its surroundings, finding only one plastic water bottle, which turns out to belong to Marcus.

00:02:44.160 --> 00:02:50.320
The story of what Marcus may, or may not, have heard is never resolved.

00:02:51.040 --> 00:03:09.600
Around the same time, SINAPROC is also searching for one of their own members, Osman Valenzuela, who participated in a search for the two missing dutch girls on April 4. Around noon the next day, Osman's body is found in a river under a bridge. Some say he drowned, others say he was murdered.

00:03:10.320 --> 00:03:24.760
Years later, an image which is supposed to have been found on the phone of Osman Valenzuela, turns up on Internet forums, and all to soon the rumor goes around that the picture shows Kris and Lisanne, swimming with Osman and one other person.

00:03:25.760 --> 00:03:40.880
Although the whole story of the swimming photo is successfully debunked by Christian Hardinghaus and Annette Nenner in their book 'Still Lost in Panama' these old rumors die hard and even today the photo is still frequently associated with Kris and Lisanne.

00:03:43.200 --> 00:03:59.360
Meanwhile, as the days drag by without any news, the hundreds of men and women who search the mountains around Boquete start to loose hope. There is no place left they have not searched, if Kris and Lisanne are anywhere in this area, they should have found them long ago!

00:04:02.760 --> 00:04:22.960
For a short moment, some hope returns when on April 10 a small white bag and, right next to it, a pink insole are found in a remote area of the mountains between the Pedra de Lino trail and the Pianista trail on the Pacific side of the continental divide, a place where few tourists will ever go.

