00:08:55.200 --> 00:09:03.960
Due to the original optimism that the two girls were lost on the mountain and would be found soon enough, the police is also desperately late and running behind the events.

00:09:05.000 --> 00:09:16.240
There are rumors that Kris and Lisanne were visible on several CCTV camera's, but the tape of these camera's appears to have been overwritten by the time the police finally requests the footage.

00:09:17.280 --> 00:09:33.720
Although an initial inspection was carried out earlier, a full forensic search of the bedroom of the two girls is only carried on on April 8, one week after their appearance, and by that time so many people have been walking in and out of this room and so many items have been touched or moved that little can be learned from this.

00:09:34.480 --> 00:09:55.240
Perhaps even more surprising, the hard disks of the computers at the language school, which contain the all important browser history of the searches, are only removed for inspection on April 10 and by that time so many other people have been working on these PC's that no conclusive data is ever gained from this inspection.

00:09:56.120 --> 00:10:13.320
Logging's of mobile phone connections from the various cell phone towers in the area, which could be vital in tracking down the movements of the two girls, are only requested on April 8, one week after the disappearance, and once again no useful data is ever obtained from this.

00:10:14.080 --> 00:10:30.000
After initial interviews on April 3, important further interviews are undertaken only on April 8, although sadly many important witnesses are never interviewed, and many of the questions asked are rather weird to say the least, and the same can be said about the answers!

00:10:31.000 --> 00:10:49.600
For this video, it would take too long to go into details on all the peculiarities of these interviews, but on her YouTube site and blog, Scarlet has done a fantastic job in analyzing each affidavit, and we strongly encourage all of you to check these on her site. Links can be found in the description of this video.

00:10:51.200 --> 00:11:15.960
All in all, international confidence that the Panamanian police is going to solve this case quickly is not high, and as the days pass by, former dutch police officer Erik Westra suspects Kris and Lisanne may have accidentally witnessed drugs trafficking on the Pianista trail, while others come up with other theories, many of which the Panamanian authorities would probably prefer to keep out of the spotlights.

00:12:18.000 --> 00:12:39.000
Compared to other cities in Panama, crime rates in Boquete are moderate, however a quick search on Internet is sufficient to find a long list of allegations, and while the police is struggling to find any evidence, the assembled press has a field day in publishing the most gruesome scenario's. There is no doubt this is hurting all those who depend on tourism for their income.

00:12:39.720 --> 00:12:59.080
Given this situation it is probably not surprising that on April 22 the Personería Municipal Boquete is relieved of the case and the chief public prosecutor's office of the third judicial district of Chiriquí, based in David, takes over, with Betzaida Pittí Cerrud investigating a crime involving the deprivation of liberty and kidnapping.

00:13:00.000 --> 00:13:18.920
Years later, Pitti will claim that this was a political decision and that she was set up to fail, and she may well be correct in this, however there is also a lot of criticism on the way she handles this case, and in her first interview, the task she sets herself is rather surprising.

00:13:28.320 --> 00:13:46.000
We will come back to this toward the end of this episode, however in general: if you start a police investigation on a crime, one would expect that the prime task is to arrest the perpetrator and solve the case, however there is not a word on this and all she mentions is finding the girls!

00:13:47.040 --> 00:13:56.800
With the case still in limbo without the slightest trace of the two girls, the highly unusual decision is made on April 27 to fly a dutch police team out to Panama.

00:14:34.360 --> 00:15:00.720
In an interview from April 28, Lisanne's brother Martijn is still showing the route to Casa Pedro as the most likely route taken, the same route which is also strongly promoted by Ingrid, the head of the language school. But in a later article, Betzaida Pitti will write she almost instantly dismissed this whole theory as the description the owner of Casa Pedro gave of the two girls does not match their actual appearances.

